### One Constraint to Resolve First

The `Cluster` model stores `image_name` (filename string). `Photo` stores `optimized_filename`. **Confirm these match exactly** — same filename, same extension. If they differ (e.g. cluster stores `raw_abc.jpg`, photo stores `opt_abc.webp`), you need a normalization step in the JOIN before writing any backend code. This is the single dependency everything else hangs on.

