What Was Fixed & How
1. 🔢 Cluster Flood (400 clusters for 102 photos) — tasks.py + clustering_service.py
Root cause: The clustering threshold was 0.62 — too loose. Every face even slightly different got its own cluster. With group photos where the same person appears at different angles, lighting or partially occluded, you get explosive cluster counts.
Fix: Raised threshold from 0.62 → 0.72 in tasks.py. At this level, ArcFace embeddings reliably merge the same person across varied shots. Also improved the search to check top-3 nearest neighbours instead of just top-1, making merging more robust. For 100 photos you should now see 20–60 clusters instead of 400.

2. 👥 Friends Tab Same as Your Photos — search_service.py
Root cause: The old logic was broken — it found images in matching clusters, then added to friend_images but never excluded photos where the user appears. Result: same photos in both tabs.
Fix — complete rewrite of friends logic:

user_image_names = all photos where YOU appear
For each of your matched cluster_ids, find ALL photos containing that cluster's face
From those, exclude any image where you appear
The remainder = truly different photos, same co-attendees → Friends Nearby

The two tabs are now guaranteed disjoint — no photo can appear in both.

3. 🎬 Scene Labels — Normalized & Deduplicated — event_routes.py
Root cause: Raw Places365 labels like office, office_cubicles, cafeteria, restaurant were all showing as separate filter chips. Plus irrelevant labels like parking_lot, butchers_shop, nursing_home appeared.
Fix:

HIDDEN_SCENE_LABELS — 30+ noisy labels never shown
SCENE_CANONICAL — maps similar raw labels to one canonical name (e.g., office + office_cubicles both → "Office")
/events/{id}/scenes endpoint now deduplicates by canonical name and caps at 12 chips
/events/{id}/clusters?scene= endpoint added — proper server-side scene filtering with pagination


